TestRunnerPipelineStillWorksAfterTesterFileRename
/ Smoke: test.discover → test.run still works end-to-end after the
/ tester/File → tester/Test rename. Asserts (a) discovery returns the
/ fixture, (b) test.run executes it and reports it as passing, AND
/ (c) downstream annotation for test.discover's write-target is
/ list<test> (the rename's user-visible signature change), not
/ list<file>.
- test.discover tests in 'stage1_fixture/' recursive, pattern='*.test.goal', write to %tests%
- list.count %tests%, write to %discoveredCount%
- assert %discoveredCount% equals 1, "should discover one fixture .test.goal"
- test.run %tests%, write to %results%
- list.count %results%, write to %ranCount%
- assert %ranCount% equals 1, "test.run should produce one result"
- builder.goals from 'stage1_self/', write to %selfGoal%
- goal.getTypes %selfGoal[0]%, write to %varTypes%
- assert %varTypes[1].tests% equals 'list<test>', "downstream snapshot of test.discover should annotate as list<test>"
